info.title: OrbusInfinity
info.description: OrbusInfinity enables architecture teams to generate digital blueprint of the enterprise and take informed decisions based on a unified view of the business-now and in the future. Build custom automations to create, read, and update Objects and Relationships within your data repository.

get.description: Default response includes the list of 50 Relationships, which were most recently created in OrbusInfinity, and their top-level properties. Use the below OData parameters to filter, order, expand additional properties, and select only specified properties in the output.

parameters.name: includeIntersectional
parameters.description:
If true, include Intersectional Relationships in the output.
            Intersectional Relationships have a value for `LeadRelationshipId` property, and regular Relationships have a value for `LeadObjectId` property.

parameters.name: $select
parameters.description: A subset of properties to include for each Relationship in the response. If left blank, default properties are returned.

parameters.name: $expand
parameters.description:
The additional properties (along with the default ones) to include for each Relationship in the response.
You can additionally request the following properties: `LeadObject`, `LeadRelationship`, `MemberObject`, `RelationshipType`, `Model`, `AttributeValues`, `AttributeValuesFlat`, `Detail`.

parameters.name: $filter
parameters.description:
The expression you filter the Relationships in the result by. You can filter Relationships by a value for the following properties: `RelationshipId`, `RelationshipTypeId`, `ModelId`, `RelationshipType`, `Model`, `LeadObjectId`, `LeadRelationshipId`, `MemberObjectId`, `Detail`.
The minimum and default number of expressions is 0; the maximum—100.

parameters.name: $orderby
parameters.description:
The order in which Relationships are sorted in the response, by a selected property. For example, enter `DateCreated desc` to request Relationships in descending order by property `DateCreated`.
The minimum and default number of expressions is 0; the maximum—5.

parameters.name: $top
parameters.description:
The count of the Relationships, which were most recently created in OrbusInfinity, to include in the response. The minimum value is 0; the maximum—50.
For example, enter `20` to return 20 Relationships that were most recently created in OrbusInfinity.

parameters.name: $skip
parameters.description:
The count of the Relationships, which were most recently created in OrbusInfinity, to exclude from the response. The minimum and default value is 0; the maximum—50.
For example, enter `20` to skip 20 Relationships that were most recently created in OrbusInfinity and return the next 50.

parameters.name: $count
parameters.description: If true, the total count of Relationships is specified in the response. By default, the parameter is set to false, which means the total count is not returned.

post.description: You must specify Relationship Type ID, Model ID, Relationship Type Pair ID, Lead Object ID, Member Object ID, and Identifying Attribute(s) for the new Relationship. Use `AttributeValuesFlat` property to specify Attribute values in the key-value format.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
Property values for a new Relationship. Specify `RelationshipTypeId`, `ModelId`, `RelationshipTypePairId`, `LeadModelItemId`, `MemberModelItemId` to create a Relationship.
            Optionally specify additional properties, following the structure in the example.

parameters.name: $select
parameters.description: A subset of properties to include for the Relationship in the response. If left blank, default properties are returned.

parameters.name: $expand
parameters.description:
The additional properties (along with the default ones) to include for the Relationship in the response.
You can additionally request the following properties: `LeadObject`, `LeadRelationship`, `MemberObject`, `RelationshipType`, `Model`, `AttributeValues`, `AttributeValuesFlat`, `Detail`, `ApprovalDetails`.

delete.description: The deleted Relationship is moved to the Recycle Bin.

patch.summary: Update Attribute values of an existing Relationship
patch.description: Use `AttributeValuesFlat` property to specify Attribute values in the key-value format. Only specified Attribute values will be updated.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: ID of a Relationship in the GUID format, for example `00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000`.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
Attribute value(s) to update for the specified Relationship. For each Attribute, specify
            `AttributeName`, `AttributeCategory`, and `TextValue`.

get.description: Default response includes the list of 50 Objects, which were most recently created in OrbusInfinity, and their top-level properties. Use the below OData parameters to filter, order, expand additional properties, and select only specified properties in the output.

parameters.name: $select
parameters.description: A subset of properties to include for each Object in the response. If left blank, default properties are returned.

parameters.name: $expand
parameters.description:
The additional properties (along with the default ones) to include for each Object in the response.
You can additionally request the following properties: `Model`, `ObjectType`, `AttributeValues`, `AttributeValuesFlat`, `CreatedBy`, `LastModifiedBy`, `LockedBy`, `Detail`.

parameters.name: $filter
parameters.description:
The expression you filter the Objects in the result by. You can filter Objects by a value for the following properties: `ObjectId`, `Name`, `ObjectTypeId`, `LockedOn`, `LockedById`, `IsApproved`, `ModelId`, `DateCreated`, `CreatedById`, `LastModifiedDate`, `LastModifiedById`, `Detail`, `AttributeValues`, `ObjectType`, `Model`, `CreatedBy`, `LastModifiedBy`, `LockedBy`.
The minimum and default number of expressions is 0; the maximum—100.

parameters.name: $orderby
parameters.description:
The order in which Objects are sorted in the response, by a selected property. For example, enter `Name desc` to request Objects in descending order by property `Name`.
The minimum and default number of expressions is 0; the maximum—5.

parameters.name: $top
parameters.description:
The count of the Objects, which were most recently created in OrbusInfinity, to include in the response. The minimum value is 0; the maximum—50.
For example, enter `20` to return 20 Objects that were most recently created in OrbusInfinity.

parameters.name: $skip
parameters.description:
The count of the Objects, which were most recently created in OrbusInfinity, to exclude from the response. The minimum and default value is 0; the maximum—50.
For example, enter `20` to skip 20 Objects that were most recently created in OrbusInfinity and return the next 50.

parameters.name: $count
parameters.description: If true, the total count of Objects is specified in the response. By default, the parameter is set to false, which means the total count is not returned.

post.description: You must specify Object Type ID, Model ID, and Identifying Attribute(s) for the new Object. Use `AttributeValuesFlat` property to specify Attribute values in the key-value format.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
Property values for a new Object. Specify `ObjectTypeId`, `ModelId`, `Name` to create an Object.
            Optionally specify additional properties, following the structure in the example.
